class Solution {
    public int distanceTraveled(int mainTank, int additionalTank) {
        int distance = 0;
        while (mainTank > 0) {
            distance += 10 * Math.min(5, mainTank);
            mainTank -= Math.min(5, mainTank);
            if (mainTank > 0 && additionalTank > 0) {
                additionalTank -= 1;
                mainTank += 1;
            }
        }
        return distance;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the fuel consumption process, updating the distance traveled and fuel levels accordingly. It handles the transfer of fuel from the additional tank to the main tank as needed, ensuring an accurate calculation of the maximum distance. 
